dmca.title: Baby's Confused About Trademark
dmca.body:
I represent 'Babya Software Group', and recently discovered that one of your PDF documents (http://www.uhin.com/meetings/Standards/pdf/2001_0808_mins.pdf) appeared with Google search results for 'Babya System' and in this PDF file, it refers to 'BabyA'. 

I, as the author of 'Babya' programs, do not approve of the use of the word 'Babya' in your documents because I have automatic copyright in Australia for all Babya product names, and code and 'Babya' is to only be used to describe certain software made by me. Please remove the document in question within 90 days. If this has not been done, I will email your organisation with a request to remove the offending content from Google and other sources.
